Dear Sirs/Madam,I would like to first of all thank Ms Yvonne from Customer Service that called me today to follow up on my enquiry on 10th Aug 2022. She managed to put my purchase on the NDP57 (Less 57% Promotion Plan).I was travelling and returned on 10th Aug and when I saw my email on your NDP -57% promotion plan, I immediately obtained a quote for the Classic plan and included a rider to cover any driver. I was quite happy to enjoy the 57% discount but unfortunately when I proceeded with the payment and already submitted my credit card details for the check out then I realised that the quoted amount have changed as the time was just minutes past 12 midnight of 10th Aug 2022. Immediately I put a stop to the transaction and contacted the online chat but could not get a satisfactory reply, so I left a message for your return call. My point is that your system could have advised your customers 5 minutes before the cut-off rather than let the transaction take place and change the price. Or you should have honoured the quoted price since the transaction has already reached the final step of purchase! Instead your system chose to sneakily change the total amount just seconds before they hit the PAY button! I understand that your system need a rule for the cut-off mark but I must say that it was disappointing as you did not consider that the customer had already taken the implied step of payment. I would suggest that for your future promotions, if the transaction have already reached the final step of payment (credit card details already provided) your system should accept it rather than losing the sale! Your system could also prompt the customer to pay immediately in order to enjoy the discount provided the transaction is at the final check-out step. Thank you for your time to hear me out on this. Best regards.

Stupid website.Buggy process.Tried to buy travel insurance using retrieve personal details function (for existing customer) when completing the form.Process kept hanging.Unable to pay.Instructed to call 68208888.Pointless - office not yet open.Fast With Deductions.   That's what FWD Insurance stands for.If you are doing your research about FWD and starting off with reading unhappy reviews - you are a wise consumer indeed.   They have many 5 Star reviews - because the buying process was smooth, fast, efficient etc. But it's all meaningless. Why? Because any fool can devise a process that is good at taking your money. Isn't that how scammers work? How does FWD taking your money painlessly make it worthy of a 5 Star rating? Surely the BUYING of the insurance is not as important as HOW WELL the product protects you, and HOW SMOOTHLY you are able to make claims against the policy.¬† ¬†The real worth of a company is how it deals with problems - for example, PROBLEMS THE COMPANY ITSELF CAUSED, including PROBLEMS IT DOES NOT WANT TO ADMIT.   If your trip has not even started and the company cannot even issue the policy documents properly - does that not make you think how it will ever look after you, when it can't even get it's own administrative processes in order? When you buy insurance, what is the one thing you want? A receipt? Ice cream? Nasi lemak? Or a policy document?¬† ¬†Later on, they try to trivialise this event. What If they did the same to a disaster that happened to you? Insurance is a product that looks after the "What-If?" moments. But FWD Insurance themselves do not look into their own What-If events either out of sheer incompetence or just bloody laziness.I tried to buy travel insurance at 0830hrs on a normal Wednesday morning. The process failed. The failed process gave a number to call. But nobody answered. It was connected to a stupidly designed IVR system that eventually cut me off. I could not leave a message. So it was one failure after another after another.Did no one think, WHAT IF a customer tries unsuccessfully to buy a policy outside of normal office hours? Why provide a number to call that is manned only during office hours? Does it take a genius to ask WHAT IF that happens? I wasn't even buying a policy at 4 in the morning - it was 8.30.Is morale in the office so low that the staff just don't give a s**t?In their response to my feedback, they try to gloss over the "Broken Link" event as being now resolved. Yes it is resolved, but along the way EVEN MORE mistakes were made in the wake of the problem - which they conveniently left out.I'm quite sure that they do not have a ready list of those customers affected by the Broken Link incident. Why would that matter? Because if the same customer comes back again to buy another policy, he will surely NOT forget how he felt scammed the first time around he bought a policy but was given a link that did not work, if and when he again meets problems trying to buy another policy. So it would help if their system could automatically flag such aggrieved customers, and ensure that NO MORE PROBLEMS OCCUR. But of course, they did not think of this. No one at FWD Insurance cares. Devising a solution to such a What If scenario is just too much work for a company that just wants to suck your money.Update after their reply to me more than a week after my initial review - this is my reply:Irish,You still do not understand how unsatisfactory your company's service is.Your e-mail reply is proof.You gloss over the problems I experienced as a mere "Broken Link" issue. It is much more more than that.Check the e-mails from your Donna Ang timestamped 1034hrs 12 Oct 2021. She claims to have attached a pdf copy of the policy when she did not such thing.I send her a reply at 1110hrs 12 Oct 2021 pointing out this fact.She replies at 1236hrs 12 Oct 2021 and admits her mistake.Your company has a serious problem with not being able to look after details.  ONLY when you admit this problem will you be on your way to fixing it. Your email is proof that FWD insurance STILL refuses to admit that they cannot look after details.

column1: Its so painful to claim!! AVOID
column5: Its so painful to claim!!! The clauses are unreasonable! AVOID AT ALL COST.All my cash was stolen when I was overseas and I ensure that I kept my bag with me, or in the LOCKED car boot when I went for activities (diving / hiking) and FWD rejected my claim as the police report did not indicate that the cash was 100% with me throughout. I did due diligence to safeguard my belongings but FWD expects me to bring along my passport and cash into the sea?!? It could have been in the locked car or our locked Airbnb, I cannot believe they rejected this loss of money claim because it was 'unattended' despite it being kept in properly secured facilities. How unreasonable and unrealistic is this?? I even bought the more expensive plan to have better coverage - all for nothing. My friends who bought another insurer managed to claim theirs. They claimed it on reasonable grounds that we did our due diligence.

We were concerned about our insurance paying out but not only did FWD meet all its commitments and some we were pleasantly surprised with (paying for her cover while she was getting treatment) but they did in their customary fast and friendly way. We are big fans and it is a pleasure to renew with FWD.

column1: Difficult to claim from FWD Insurance
column5: I am a 58 year old man and bought an annual accident insurance online on 8th August 2020 from FWD Insurance for S$532.66. The coverage was for death benefit of S$500,000.00 with up to S$10,000.00 medical expenses for impatient and outpatient.I injured my back while doing my house spring cleaning on the 11th February 2021.  I decided not to seek medical treatment immediately as it was the eve of CNY and was going to have a reunion dinner with my family.  I endured the pain till the second day of CNY and decided to seek medical treatment at a private hospital A & E department.  The doctor said that I had sacroiliac joint pain.  He said that the pain is most likely caused by carrying a heavy object while bending and twisting my back. I had submitted an accident claim of S$203.40 for the outpatient treatment to FWD insurance but was rejected.  Below was the reply from FWD insurance.1. The incident was not considered an "accident" as     it seems like a prolonged strain on your back     during house cleaning and the pain felt later and     was not immediate.  ;2. An accident is where a sudden and one time     incident that causes the pain or injury almost     immediately; and 3. There was no evidence that an external incident     caused the pain (for example, a fall or hit by an     object).I am deeply disappointed with FWD Insurance and felt cheated that FWD Insurance rejected my claim.
GOOD & CHEAPGREAT & NO PROBLEM

Very easy to subscribe indeed, however the nightmare starts when you actually need the insurance.Took international health for both my partner and I, as we are expats without inpatient insurance.Both of us have outpatient provided by employer. Both of us consulted GP then specialists for medical conditions. When it was time to do procedures at the clinic, we were confident it'll go smooth because we took FWD with all the available top ups to even avoid any co-payment.But here you have to ask FWD for pre-authorisation. Which takes 10 business days. So you might have to reschedule your procedure. This document must be filled by the surgeon, which is impossible to contact at the hospital. However the hospital can fill the form for you in exchange of few hundred dollars, not covered by FWD. Then the pre-authorisations are denied for both of us. FWD decided that because we had met the GP through another insurer before asking FWD, our conditions were "pre-existing" and not covered by the policy.How can a condition can be pre-existing when you're asking to do screening tests? and haven't passed the test yet? You can argue for as long a you want on the phone they don't care much.So after money wasted to fill stupid papers, and 2 procedures cancelled, it is now a struggle to cancel this useless insurance, have been sending letters and emails for a months and counting.

column1: I have purchased the travel insurance from FWD
column5: I have purchased the travel insurance from FWD. The process is very intuitive and the platform is user friendly. Price wise, very affordable, only SGD 102 for 2 pax travelling to US (14 days). However, due to the COVID-19 pandemic, I have to cancel my travel plan. After gotten refund from my travel booking agent, there is a certain amount of  irrecoverable prepaid expenses. Therefore, I wrote to FWD and submitted my travel claims. FWD was very helpful and prompt, they refunded all the irrecoverable prepaid expenses to me, meaning I have gotten a FULL refund for the air fare paid. FWD is very efficient, the claim executive Kenneth Yap who handled my case was really helpful, they refunded the amount to me within 2 days.I am feeling really grateful because I understand that the outlook for the aviation and travelling market has not been good, yet FWD has been very helpful in processing the travel claim for affected customers like me. I will definitely support FWD in the future. I hope that FWD and the rest of the travel industry will get through this hardship and continue to stay strong.

column1: Best Experience with an Insurance Company - FWD
column5: Bought a travel insurance from FWD before the pandemic. Decided to cancel the trip for our team safety. Since travelling to USA requires to apply for ESTA (US Visa) we wrote in to request for a refund but was turned down by the ESTA team. So decided to make a claim from FWD. Because the visa has a validity of 2 years, the claim was unable to proceed. The officer in charge, Mr Keith Tay, helped put in my further request to refund my travel insurance since, I was eligible due to the date I bought the policy - prior to the start of the pandemic. Within the next day, I received a confirmation of refund!I am very impressed with the FWD claim team for being so understanding, sensitive and fast refund during this trying time. This is the best I had ever experienced with an insurance company! I will buy my travel insurance with FWD going forward from now and I highly recommend to all my families and friends. Great job Mr Keith Tay and the claim team! Thank you!

column1: Easy to sign up, but don't believe all the hype...
column5: Easy to sign up, but don't believe all the hype. I remember vividly telling my partner we'd now secured the top tier FWD travel insurance in July last year, which turned out to be absolutely worthless... Very rarely had to claim on any travel insurance in my life and then when I have to seek my insurer's help with big exposures to cancelled trips FWD were nowhere to be seen. They cherry picked dates as to when the WHO classified things as a know event on one claim and then used a different date on another claim in what can only be described as 'cherry picking'. They gave me a screen shot of another insurer who applied the same terms but failed to include another competitor who were much more understanding and consistent in their approach... I an a nutshell, don't believe the slick easy to sign-up process - once they have your money there is no way to look online and check the status of your claim, I had to follow up countless times despite reassurances that I would "hear back within a week"Companies (and there are a number of airlines who fall in the same camp) may survive the current turmoil but the way they've treated customers versus others in the same industry will be very evident to see when the dust settles on Covid-19.
Cannot be any clearer, and not strange terms.

column1: Claiming for travel insurance from FWD is a nightmare
column5: When attempting to make a claim for travel insurance online, the online form designed was too rigid for me to fill in any information to submit. I was compelled to cancel a trip in light of government's advisory ahead of the trip (and other reasons include: cancelled conference which was the sole purpose of the trip, and unsuccessful flight refund request), but the form doesn't allow me to indicate 'date of incident' as occurring in advance the trip. The prompt says, 'date of incident must occur during the trip'. As a result of this repeated prompt, I was unable to submit the form and had to turn to 'calling me back' function or sending my requests to generic emails which means little chance of getting back to customers. I hope they improve their online claim form format to allow for greater room of flexibility. Furthermore, even though Co-vid 19 was made a known event on 31 January, I‚Äôve purchased this policy at least a month before the unforeseen events of 1. WHO‚Äôs declaration of Covid-19 as a global pandemic and 2. Singapore government‚Äôs advisory against ALL travels. In verbatim, the FWD travel policy has explicitly mentioned that FWD will not pay for 'any claims for Trip cancellation and loss of deposit benefit and Trip postponement benefit if you buy your policy less than 3 days before your scheduled departure date.‚Äô However, I have purchased this policy at least two months before my scheduled departure date and in light of these unforeseen events. Besides, a clause in the policy document includes 'trip cancellation due to serious public events', of these unforeseen events include travel advisory by singapore government and/or WHO declaration of pandemic that occurs 30 days before the scheduled departure date.I am thus writing to request for a claim only for my flights since this policy promises to cover these unforeseeable events upon my policy purchase. I had to turn to this platform to leave a review (my first time leaving a review on a public platform) as my emails were not replied after several days, and the customer service staff on the phone was relentless in parroting Co-vid 19 as a known event without engaging my justification. I hope this review will bring to light some of the difficulties of making a claim from FWD travel insurance.

column1: Revised Review on my FWD travel insurance
column5: This is a revised review: FWD responded to by query/review titled: Utterly Disappointed with FWD Travel Insurance, after 11 days with a more comprehensive clarification and highlighted the conditions for the claims to be accepted. Subsequently they reviewed my claim and accepted it. While I was disappointed by their initial non-response, I applaud their follow up and goodwill gesture. Thus raised the rating from 1 to 4 stars. Initial Review:I had bought a travel insurance with FWD for my Bangladesh trip from Singapore in Feb. While I was in Bangladesh, my travel agent informed me my return connecting flight from Bangkok to Singapore was cancelled and they could only offer me another flight in the next morning ( more than 12 hours later than my scheduled flight). I had no choice as I already paid in full for the ticket. I submitted a claim for flight delay with the necessary supporting documents to FWD after returning home. After 2 email correspondence, FWD replied that as I was notified by the agent  more than 24 hours before departure, I was not qualified for the claim. I read again the policy and no where did I find any clause about the 24 hour window. I sent them another email asking for clarification but no response for almost 2 weeks. I was left with a very bad impression that FWD charges a very low premium to lure customers but will find all the excuses to reject a claim without valid explanation. I am happy if someone in the insurance industry can enlighten me about this clause or is it just another stupid excuse as FWD is not taking my query seriously

I'm not one to leave a poor review. In fact, I don't think I've ever done it before but I am left feeling helpless now. This morning I called to seek assistance with flight refunds as I am unable to continue with my trip. My sister passed away 2 weeks ago and I have a trip scheduled for April. I cannot leave my family or think about travelling during this period yet the agent who spoke with me didn't even seem to try finding a solution for me. I even had to share the nature of death in hopes that she would understand or take it more seriously. I was just given a single sentence response - "I'm sorry but our policy only covers 30 days from event and since your trip is in April we can't do anything." She did not sound unpleasant but she did sound inexperienced and put me on hold to check (with whom, I don't know)I'm not sure what she claims as event, the death of my sister or my trip. I'm really disappointed in FWD. I wrote in with confidence that you would be able to assist me. A friend encouraged me to do so as his was a success story. His insurance provider did help with claims when he lost a loved one. Obviously, not FWD. This is my 2nd time purchasing your travel insurance and thought you would show more heart in handling my case. I am struggling to get in touch with the airlines due to the virus situation and it's upsetting that I'm put on the back burner due to travelers cancelling trips everywhere. I'm here trying to get help for something completely different. Please understand that not everyone deals with grief in 30 days and you don't expect everyone to shake it off and travel within 30 days. Death is unexpected and nobody is prepared for it. I have a family to look after and other commitments that came with my sister's passing. I don't wish to name your agent. I'm just writing this with a very heavy heart. It would help if you could share where your policy states that I am unable to claim in my current situation as I cannot find it on your website. Thank you.

Loooong reply later (they exceeded the timeline), they replied and requested for the documents I‚Äôve uploaded as well as ridiculous additions Eg a German-Eng translation of my uploaded DB train e-ticket & receipt. Their follow up response is ridiculously long and insensitive. You can sense they are not interested in your welfare. I decided to contact the travel service providers eg airlines and guess what, I got refund promptly (less than a week) with the same documents I submitted to FWD which they deem insufficient. Seriously, how often will one cancel a trip due to emergency hospitalisation and a parent‚Äôs demise?! Pls do NOT waste your time with FWD.

column1: Claims Exp and Customer Service Exp
column5: Travel Insurance (Claims) - The product itself is just mehhh because the way 30 days from return of the trip was counted very different from what I understood and how some of the other insurers would have explained. I took a night flight back and touched down on 16/10/2019, 11:05pm but FWD treated it as that I was already back in SG for an entire day of 16th. Perhaps, I misunderstood how days should be counted. Despite the above, the claims handler (Joyee) for my Parent travel claim is really good with what she does. Prompt replies, Explanations given and she also advices well on the next step / requirements. When she explained on why one of the claim would not be payable, she went the extra mile to check with the management, but the management still rejected it. Term Life Insurance -Benjamin (I dont know which dept but he is the dude that replies on the webchat) & Tracy from the Customer Engagement Team is very helpful. After the purchase of the Term Life Insurance for my parent previously, FWD system did not send out the 'welcome E-mail'. The both of them assisted me from the start to the end of the whole process. Which includes all the 'silly' questions that I had to ask to re-verify after reading the wordings. So, after all the MILLIONS of questions i have asked, I finally bought it. In conclusion, the reliability of the product, i am not very sure. The only thing that I am sure of is the customer service which is really AWESOME! The one missing star is for the rejected claim which I still really REALLY disagree on and the 4 stars is for the assistance that Joyee, Benjamin and Tracy have helped out with. THANK YOU SO MUCH, YOU 3 WONDERFUL PEOPLE!!

column1: FWD Helped with my accident claim.
column5: On 6 November a truck driver rear-ended my car as I was turning into my condo complex. He acknowledged fault and fortunately, no one was hurt. But, the sheer hassle of dealing with an accident was not something I was looking forward to... the loss of time, money, effort, etc.I was pleasantly surprised upon calling the FWD accident helpline. The agent was great and first asked if everyone involved was OK. He then clearly took me through the steps that I would need to take and guided me to the nearest FWD- approved garage. Within 2 1/2  hours of the accident, I was at the Progressive Auto garage, the accident report was filed and they gave me a loaner car to drive home. What could have been hugely difficult and time-consuming - was made very simple and fast. Thanks FWD for great customer service!

column1: In terms of customer service engagement
column5: In terms of products, FWD is good. However, once the sale is made, the customer engagement team will ruin all the possible good connections you may have had with the brand. It is my regret to have recommended FWD to my family. My sister-in-law started this horrendous journey with an insincere operator who apparently just wanted her to repeat herself without being heard. Subsequently, there were also no follow-up done as promised on their end. Later, she and her husband had to put in hours and hours, days and months following up on their own efforts just to make sure things were right. If the note was to call after 5.30pm, FWD will call prior without respecting your note, nor your time. Eventually after months of torment when the head of customer service can finally be reached, this supposed leader of the department showed no remorse in their lack of professionalism and competence.Not all, but most of the encountered staff under customer service were extremely presumptuous and insincere. The follow ups made were not to serve the customers but for them to defend their mistakes and argue their points without listening to the customer. I was beside my sister-in-law when the head of customer service called. I couldn‚Äôt believe what I heard: the head of customer service offered solutions that she was not going to deliver nor honour. She also ridiculously suggested in the conversation that my sister-in-law and her husband had credit issues when the problem in case was completely non-credit related. It was the most absurd thing I have ever heard the head of anything said, having it being completely irrelevant and inaccurate. Perhaps the head of customer service was experiencing some credit issues herself, but we would like to have someone who can separate their personal issues and deal with the problem objectively. It makes us wonder what is this department for. We really regret using FWD after all these experiences with the ludicrous customer engagement team. Such shameful behaviours of theirs were the least and last we had expected. Be warned.Response to reply: Lina Zulkifli as the head of the department to be of as said above is definitely unprofessional, let alone proper of the job title. Thanks for your reply to ascertain our points. This is evidently nothing assuring.

column1: Wasn't informed of risk of reduced sum assured prior to cancellation of policy.
column5: Received email for anniversary promo code of 33% for existing members so decided to replace existing plan TERM LIFE & CANCER plan. 1) Called in to enquire about the replacement of policies but was left forgotten for weeks by Marrisa. 2) Wasn't inform that there are possibility or risk of my coverage being reduced even though my health is still in good with nothing to declare. Was only told that i have to undergo 90 days of waiting period which i agreed to. 3) After my 2 policies being cancelled, got a shocked to find out that underwriter reduced my Term Plan 10165362 - Critical Illness coverage by 200K. Wasn't satisfied with the outcome. Client should be notified of the risk of replacing policy tho is the same plan. Had wasted alot of time follow up on this.

column1: My Harman Kardon Wireless Speakers was‚Ä¶
column5: My Harman Kardon Wireless Speakers was damaged during my recent travel trip. Took them 10 days to reply to my claims and FWD conveniently pulled out their clauses and blamed this as mechanical fault. I wrote in to seek clarifications and since 2 weeks till now there was zero reply from them.For those who want to pay peanuts and get monkeys - FWD is the brand. Cheaper Premium and Repudiate Liability is their Motto.(Consumers out there, you've been warned)This was the exact reply.Greetings from FWD!Travel insurance plan protects travellers against unforeseen events including medical emergencies, flight delays and theft or damage to your personal belongings. We note that the item (Speaker) malfunctioned (buzzing sound & turn on/off)  which is more related to mechanical failure. As such we regret to inform that the claim is not successful, due to the following reason;-	There is no accidental damage to the item and no external visible damage.Policy Wording:Travel-Insurance-Contract-2604201We acknowledge that this may not be the outcome you wanted but hope you will accept our decision nonetheless. If you require further assistance or have any other questions, please contact us at 6820 8888.Thank You.

Sorry I rated a 5 star but not sure why it was published as 2star & I made changes. In my 25years in travel trade and a travel insurance believer. This is my 1st hospitalisation claim and post medical.After my trip to Ladakh in an high altitude environment 11,000-18,000feet above sea level that I could not climatize since landed and endured for 11days till home. I checked into A&E that late night and was asked to be warded immediately. I called several times for that 2 days to emergency helpline & customer support staff. Customer support Staff named Benjamin and another gentlemen in the team was very assuring that I suffered after my trip and told me to take care not to worry too much and informed me on the maximise claimable. I suffered 3 complications with severe back rash, my Low blood count and myHeart was irregular that leads to every week filled with 3 doctors‚Äô appointments per week in July till early Aug. I submitted directly to your office and Keith Tay  attended to my claims. He was very professional and advise accordingly. When I finally furnished all 3 doctors‚Äô verification of my conditions and he called to update immediately on payment will be in process followed by email.  Post Service is Vital for Travel Insurance and you have just won a loyal customer after these great service.Thank you Keith Tay Great Service & good Job!Benjamin, thank you for assuring a worrying patient pending for operation any moment.

Although, my first claim took almost a month since I think their claims submission via app was not that reliable, my claim was not promptly attend. However, upon follow up with their agent, it was swiftly resolved. My second claim, I went straight to email their claims department, and the resolution was well within 2 weeks. I‚Äôm satisfied with the service and will continue to use FWD for my Travel insurance.

column1: I would give it 6 stars if I can
column5: I signed up with FWD Motor Policy last year.  The process was smooth, simple and its pricing, cost efficient.  To add icing to the cake, it also came with NCD complimentary protector.  All considered,  I am happy to give it 5 stars but a year on since, I think I would give them 6 stars if I can.  The extra star come from the excellent customer service that I received from their cust. care staff, Ms Koki.  I had a 1hr 15min telephone call with her today as I had many questions.  She completely blew me away with her patience during the marathon call, her consistent cheerfulness from start to finish, which make you feel that the company appreciates you as a customer and her genuinely helpful attitude in making sure that you truly get the help you needed. Top class after-sales service by Ms Koki and her team.  I moved here from Aunty Lucy.   I feel it pointless to even want to make detail comparison.     An ex-Minister once said, we should strive to be Cheaper, Better and Faster.   In my opinion, these attributes befits FWD.   I am definitely a happier customer today for Motor Policy.

column1: My travel claim process went through but dissatisfactory
column5: I had 2 claim experiences with FWD Travel insurance.1st) It was a small claim for luggage delayed, which was straight forward. The process went smoothly.2) The 2nd claim was for my camera which was impacted in an accident and incurred repair cost of <$4xx. I provided all the requested photo and documents. To my surprise the reimbursement was for the min rate of $50. Due to the depreciation formula which FWD used and resulted my gear worth zero value. Despite in the summary benefits of my "Business" policy it stated: "Damage to personal belongings S$500/item". Lesson learned - really need to pay extra attention to the fine prints, as different companies approach differently. Because of my bad experience, I researched and asked around, realized that for the similar cases, other insurance companies honour & paid per repair bill (up to the policy limit), or referenced market value of the item. But, valued a property to nothing or zero value, FWD was the only one I have found out. I

column1: My Claim experience with FWD Singapore- Travel insurance
column5: It is easy to buy but most difficult company to get your legitimate claim. ( trip postponement -SGD 500 only) . Based on policy document, I am legitimate to claim under trip postponement. all supporting document is attached. However, claim department justify by personal explain which is not inside policy document to deny my claim.Refer to the publish from me a few days ago. Further on , I had a few email exchange with FWD SINGAPORE claim department Mr Joel Yeo and 1 hour telephone discussion. Both parties explain our point of view. FWD underwriter realise my suggestion that  there are some space to improve policy document. They accepted my trip postponement legimate claim request. Overview the whole process, FWD SINGAPORE claim department response to client in a efficient manner. If there r discrepancy in terms of policy understanding, they are willing to listen to client ‚Äòs point view. That is highly appreciated. At the same time, claim department is able to talk to underwriter efficiently. This is also a appreciated point. Overall, FWD SINGAPORE is a trusted brand. They honor what is written on their policy document. Even the policy document certain clauses like trip postponement, the wording is not perfectly the same intension as they design the product. They r able to listen and take action for product improvement. This is my truthful and honest feedback on travel insurance claim - USA . 8 . Tripostponent due to serious public event ( natural disaster - snowstorm) claim experiences.

1. I like the chat function which it does not disappear when I was chatting with your agent while working on inputting my details on your website, and also switching to different part of your website.2. The flexibility of the motorcycle insurance, such as any authorized rider and not capping the age limit is a great selling point. A couple of insurance providers in Singapore capped the age to 65 yrs old. This is ridiculous given most people who can afford big bikes after 65 are usually safe riders, and wealth affluent. FWD is brilliant in this way.3. Only two cons that I see:a) the premium offered by FWD is extremely high, especially for bikes older than 5 years old. b) We can't coincide the policy end date to coincide with road tax renewal. It will help us to remember on renewing both mandatory payments at the same time.

column1: Feedback on LKH's application for cancer coverage
column5: 1.  Email inviting cancer policy mentioned it was a test run and survey but didn't mention it's a commitment to insure when the participant participants in the test run/survey.  Test run/survey lasted only 2 days, but that falls over the weekend and if any participant has any question on the application form, he won't get a reply from FWD till after the weekend, thereby frustrating and defeating the effectiveness of the test run/survey.2.  No clarity whether the premium discount is only for the first year or extends to annual renewals too3.  No mention whether we are allowed to change payment frequency method in future years 4.  Your staff Miss Koki called on 3Dec18 to clarify items 1 & 2 above, and promised to call again at 4pm same day to check whether I have any further problems with the application form.  No call was received from her5.  Miss Wati called today (8Dec18) to check whether I had any further questions and to advise the 35% discount ends tomorrow.  I appreciate that but I was awaiting reply to my 2nd email (see item 3 above) which she claimed FWD didn't receive.  Based on my email records, my 2nd email was successfully sent.

Cheapest travel insurance policy available most of the time but very bad service when it comes to following up and executing on travel insurance claims. Had to cut our trip short by a few days due to a medical emergency at home. Had to forego our paid hotel bookings and thought we could claim for our return flight bookings on another airline after reading the terms and conditions in the policy. Came back and submitted our claims and it took a month without any reply. Had to keep calling the company from then onwards to check on the status. It seems all travel insurance claims are managed by a third party which led to further delays. Kept getting passed from one inept claims executive to another. After taking almost 6 months, claim was denied even after submission of medical reports from hospital and other required documents. Those who intend to use FWD better pay a few dollars extra and use other insurance companies.

column1: Easy to buy, sure... but have you tried claiming?
column5: [Edited 12 July]I had an issue with my luggage-related claim with FWD's travel insurance as it took three months to be processed. (I have been buying travel insurance for all my travels for years - which are at least three times every year - and had only ever claimed once 6 years ago, which took less than two weeks to be settled through Tokyo Marine). Therefore, I had initially rated 1 star here as it seems unfounded for a valid claim to take that long; I thought I was being scammed by an online insurance company.To be fair in reviewing, I've edited this review to update that I have finally received a call yesterday from FWD settling it and explaining that they had a high volume of claim due to the travel season, hence the time gap in response. The CS contact on the line was very sincere and apologetic; they reviewed the case and we settled it all within the day.I feel that I should give them the benefit of doubt and update this review to reflect the situation. I have given four stars because I feel resolved issues are efforts made to improve things and FWD has really fast service recovery once the issue that had fallen through the cracks is resurfaced up. I really appreciate that.For those who had similar issues with claim processing time during the high peak travel season, I'd recommend giving them a call. It seems that the CS over the phone is a lot more efficient than the CS through emails.

column1: My insurance was up for renewal in a‚Ä¶
column5: My insurance was up for renewal in a few days with the Early Bird discount ending soon. Experienced tech problems on the weekend before the EB ended. Since it was a weekend, I couldnt contact their customer service hotline so I resigned myself to having to pay morethe next day. Called their hotline the next day and spoke to Eric Jiang who was very helpful in solvjng the issue. He managed to get approval to reinstate my EB discount even when he could have just gave the "sorry, you missed the deadline" line. Here's the real kicker; we tried and tried till i also lost my Special discount. So without these 2 discounts, my premium increased again. When I finally made payment, Eric emailed me saying he will also reinstate both my Special and EB discount and to expect the refund within 2 days. Great experience. Thanks Eric!

column1: Buy easy, Claiming sucks - they outsource to 3rd party - complex, unreliable  beat around the bush, messy
column5: Most of the reviews here seems to be about purchase. Yes, when it comes to purchasing the package, they are quick and fast to get their money from you. But if you are buying insurance for the assurance that you can get your claims covered promptly, reliability - FWD sucks big time for claims! . I submitted two separate travel claims - one online and one to their email claims acc a week apart and they can mixed them up into one claim. Furthermore, it took them 2 weeks to reply back to me (their simple 2 days turnaround is no where visible). They outsource their claims to 3rd party making it even more complex. Manager promise to follow up n call me me within a week at a fixed time but did not call back- totally unreliable. The FWD claims n their outsource parties keep pushing things between them. there is no one single source of contact to speak to. i hv to do the chasing myself.  Keep asking for additional documents - some documents were already furnished in the initial submission (they somehow ‚Äúlost‚Äù them?! - messy!) I should hv stayed with my Aviva. plse avoid them ‚Äî their prizes and marketing gimmicks to lure customers to sign up with them are masking their aweful unreliable claims processing!
